        Retrieve the result of a SPARQL select query as a table model.
        Parameters:
        rep - the repository to use
        query - a valid SPARQL SELECT query
        resolveNamespaces - boolean flag, to specifiy if abbreviated namespaces should be resolved
        resolveValue - the value to use as replacement for ??
        valueConfig - a FValue.ValueConfig to define how values shall be treated
        Returns:
        a populated table model
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        org.openrdf.query.QueryEvaluationException

        Return a table model for the query with the specified singleRowAction. A single row action is added as an additional column to each row. See class documentation for details.
        Parameters:
        rep - the repository to evaluate the query on
        query - the SPARQL SELECT query
        resolveNamespaces - flag to determine if namespaces should be resolved
        resolveValue - the value to resolve for, i.e. the value that is inserted into the query for ??, can be null
        valueCfg - maintain value information, such as the ImageResolver
        singleRowAction - optional list of RowActions which are applied (can be null)
        ceCtx -
